archimate:DataObject.name: Chip
archimate:DataObject.documentation: This is a concrete class that models different types of chips that are either directly configurable by the end-user (e.g.; a programmable device) and/or represent FRUs (e.g.; a special ASIC that can be upgraded by replacing it with a new version of that same ASIC). Note that capacity characteristics (e.g.; how much memory can a Flash chip hold) are defined through the PhysicalCapacity association.
